transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi. I'm trying to make a purchase with ScoreBlue.

Speaker 1: And then they asked me if I wanted to double it, and I did.

Speaker 2: So I have eight transactions. I made one.

Speaker 1: Can I get your name for the code?

Speaker 2: Charles Stiglmayer, 14224.

Speaker 1: Clinton Street?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: So when you double the order, it bills as two separate transactions, but you did double the order.

Speaker 2: Do you want me to cancel the doubling of the order?

Speaker 1: Well, what was the original, 59?

Speaker 2: No, the upgrade is 59.40. The original charges are the 113.95.

Speaker 1: So for 113, that was for 25 pills?

Speaker 2: That's the price for the 25 with the pharmacy fee, and then all the other, like, tax or whatever.

Speaker 1: And then the additional 25 was 59.40.

Speaker 2: If you don't want the additional 25, I can still cancel it.

Speaker 1: No, I'll take it, but I only want them transactions to go through one time each.

Speaker 2: I have several different emails saying I made a transaction, and it looks like I made several transactions.

Speaker 1: Yes, because you paid for 25 pills at 113.95, and when you accepted the extra 25 pills, that's a second transaction.

Speaker 2: You've only made two transactions with us, but it's all going to come in one pill bottle.

Speaker 1: Okay, I don't know if you understand. I got the...

Speaker 2: I do understand, sir. You're not listening to me.

Speaker 1: When you add the upgrade, it charges you in a separate transaction. It's not all on one transaction.

Speaker 2: I get that. I get that.

Speaker 1: But I have an email for 113. My next email is for 113. My next email is for a dollar.

Speaker 2: I guess that's a Google fee.

Speaker 1: Then it says I made an international transaction. There's another dollar.

Speaker 2: Then I have one for 59.40.

Speaker 1: I'm not the credit card company, sir. Some of those aren't us. We charge you two times.

Speaker 2: I just got off the phone with the credit card company. They told me to call you.

Speaker 1: We charge you two times, sir. I don't know how many times I can tell you this.

Speaker 2: 113.95 and 59.40. We've charged you two times. I'm looking right at it.

Speaker 1: Okay. I just want to make sure that's all there is.

Speaker 2: I promise you.

Speaker 1: Okay. Thank you very much.

Speaker 2: Have a good one.
